Excellent! 🎉 **Your settings.json is now clean and modular!**

## ✅ **What Just Happened:**

- **Old settings.json** → Safely backed up
- **New modular settings.json** → Now active
- **All configuration** → Organized in separate files
- **No manual steps needed** → Config manager handled everything

## 🎯 **Your Clean Architecture:**

```json
{
  "model": "opusplan",
  "hooks": {
    "import": ".claude/hooks/manifest.json"      // All hook logic
  },
  "projectConfig": {  
    "import": ".claude/config/project.json"     // Project settings
  },
  "debug": {
    "import": ".claude/config/debug.json"       // Debug & env vars
  }
}
```

Now Claude Code will read your settings from the modular files, keeping your main `settings.json` clean and organized! 🚀
